  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To achieve the performance it is needed to do the mapping of code and data properly"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "So, Where to keep the Share buffer ? DLMU of an Core where Write access from other cores would be 5 and read cycles would be 7"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "We need to keep Core 0 more efficient. So the memory which is accessed by Core 0 more frequently, better to keep it DLMU0. If this memory is not sufficient we will also use DLMU1 for sgared memory"
    },
